        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1483643141" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3764766057424957062">&quot;History is more full of the examples of the faithfulness of dogs than of men.&quot; - Voltaire<br/><br/><br/>I LOVED this book until....<br/><br/>and then I just could NOT continue with it !!!!!!!!!!!<br/><br/>BUT I DID !!!<br/><br/>...and I found I didn&apos;t give a damn about UNTIL...<br/>I just LOVED and enjoyed it as much as I had before.<br/><br/>I thought I probably would have done the same things Farley Mowat was accused of,<br/>having had to work with a lot of Fully Fledged Idiots in the NSW Public School System<br/>who had no compunction whatsoever about lying, t</span>
  <span id="freeText3764766057424957062" style="display:none">"History is more full of the examples of the faithfulness of dogs than of men." - Voltaire<br /><br /><br />I LOVED this book until....<br /><br />and then I just could NOT continue with it !!!!!!!!!!!<br /><br />BUT I DID !!!<br /><br />...and I found I didn't give a damn about UNTIL...<br />I just LOVED and enjoyed it as much as I had before.<br /><br />I thought I probably would have done the same things Farley Mowat was accused of,<br />having had to work with a lot of Fully Fledged Idiots in the NSW Public School System<br />who had no compunction whatsoever about lying, taking credit for other people's ideas,<br />destroying reputations of both teachers and students, the list goes on.<br />This happens in many work places.<br />Probably Most.<br />I learned how to survive by manipulating these people who were generally in the Upper echelons, <br />in the executive. One way was by matching their lies with my own. It worked very well. And I suspect that this was probably one way Farley managed to survive and undermine the Idiots running his Government Department. <br />You will meet them in the first chapter of "Never Cry Wolf."<br />You will also meet the Hunters and Officials who lied to the Government Department about wolves.<br />There is probably a Forest of Lies in this book and I have no way of untangling them.<br /><br />Let it be said however that this is one of the most enjoyable Pack of Lies or Not that I have read in a long, long time.<br />And I am now wondering whether I should be pressing "Hide entire review because of spoilers" but considering the number of people on Goodreads who think that telling the plot of the book is a review and Not a spoiler, I think I will leave it just as it is and say that just about everything I've written here is a Big Fat Lie and that the plot of which this review says NOT a Word...another lie...<br />was one of the most enjoyable I've read or not in a long, long while !!! even if I've said it before.<br /><br />You will just LOVE and be AMAZED by the wolves.<br />And I wonder sometimes if Farley lied about them to save them.<br />I would back him ALL the Way .<br /><br />P.S. I am NOW trying to discover what it was exactly that Farley has been accused of!!!<br /><br />I SHALL RETURN.</span>
